What is fillna()?

fillna() is used to replace missing values (NaN, None) in a DataFrame or Series with a specified value or method.

✅ Used for data cleaning
✅ Prevents data loss (unlike dropna())
✅ Very common in real‑world datasets

df.fillna(value)

 Forward Fill (ffill)
Uses the previous value
df.fillna(method="ffill")

Backward Fill (bfill)
Uses the next value
df.fillna(method="bfill")

Fill with Limit (Number of Replacements)
df.fillna(method="ffill", limit=1)

| Method           | Use Case                      |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------- |
| `fillna(0)`      | Replace missing with constant |
| `fillna(mean)`   | Numeric data                  |
| `method="ffill"` | Time‑series data              |
| `method="bfill"` | Next known value              |
| `limit`          | Restricted filling            |
| `inplace=True`   | Modify original DF            |
